s identity IS its type name, derived once and lowered to lowercase (camelCase) in code while the type stays PascalCase (struct Entry's Kind reference -> field kind: Kind). Type declarations are visibility-tagged Public(name,value) or Private(name,value): Public is exported for library use; Private, local, and inline are not. An inline PascalCase type in a field is sugar — derive the field name from the type, log the inline type as a Private local declaration (module-local non-exported Rust type).|] High Medium Zero [assembled-schema struct type-declaration field-name rust])) (bybe ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [|A newtype in the assembled schema is a single-element brace with just the wrapped type — (Public Topic { String }), not a derived field name. TypeValue carries a distinct Newtype(TypeReference) variant: brace with one element lowers to Newtype; alternating name-type pairs lower to Struct. Rust emits a tuple-struct pub struct Topic(pub String) with NotaTransparent (Topic([foo]) and topic.0). Surface @-syntax: Topic@String or Topic@{ String }.|] High Medium Zero [newtype assembled-schema type-value rust nota-transparent])) (utaa ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [Assembled-schema scalar built-ins are named in full English: Integer, Boolean, String — never Bool, U64, or abbreviations. Any further scalar built-ins follow the same full-English rule. Text is reserved for a possible future string-with-spaces variant; String is the scalar in use now.] High Medium Zero [assembled-schema scalar full-english-naming])) (b05y ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [|The schema language handles only the workspace Rust subset: named-field structs, named-variant enums (bare, data-carrying, struct-variant, nested), newtype (single-unnamed-field) structs, and scalar primitives (unit enums, booleans, integers, strings, vectors). No tuples — tuples are poorly-defined structs and excluded; no multi-field tuple structs, anonymous tuples, or field-less anonymous types. Strings are conceptually vectors of characters behind boxed storage; domain concepts should be typed beyond raw String (typed-string newtypes), and EnumIdentifier is a core constrained-string type.|] High Medium Zero [schema rust-subset newtype scalar enum-identifier])) (2dzp ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [|Composite type constructors are NOTA-layer datatype objects that schema reads, not schema-only sugar: the collection macros are Vec, Option, and KeyValue (not Map — risks reading as a verb — nor KeyValueMap; KeyValue is followed by key type then value type). Vector sugar is structurally a single-field container object. NOTA does not own type declarations; schema does — plain NOTA / type-reference positions can name scalars or composites (String, Vec) without declaring a new type, while declarations use positional struct, enum, and newtype forms.|] Medium Minimum Zero [nota schema key-value vector option type-reference])) (wvpg ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Principle [Schema enum variants are themselves enums or data-carrying enums — mandatory two-layer enum-of-enums structure] High Minimum Zero [schema enum])) (i8wt ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Decision [A schema declares its roots at one designated point only — the named entry-point set generalizing fixed input/output into a roots collection; nesting adds no further roots. Everything else is a free datatype declared in the namespace and referenced by roots at some position. This shapes the assembled schema as a roots section plus a free-datatype-declarations section, matching the operator roots model.] High Medium Zero [schema roots free-datatype namespace])) (hrte ([(Technology (Software (Data Modeling)))] Correction [A schema root header is a bare list of PascalCase names for Input and Output roots — each name is both the operation/reply vocabulary and an exported top-level type that library consumers import and that re